OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FIt comes as the firm urged customers
OL,8,Fto use water for essential purposes
OL,9,Fonly ` for drinking, washing and
OL,10,Fcooking, as supply issues continued
OL,11,Ffrom over the hot bank holiday weekend.
OL,13,FSouth East Water said 8,000 properties
OL,14,Fin Whitstable had no tap water, and
OL,15,Fwhile parts of the town have seen
OL,16,Fsupplies return, people are warned it
OL,17,Fcould "remain intermittent over the
OL,18,Fweekend".
OL,26,@yD@GOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FIncident manager Steve Benton
OL,8,Fapologised to customers and said the
OL,9,Fstorage areas for the Whistable area
OL,10,Fwere at "critical level" because of
OL,11,F"extremely high demand during the very
OL,12,Fhot weather".
OL,14,FHe said 14,000 properties were
OL,15,Fexperiencing low pressure or an
OL,16,Fintermittent supply in Tankerton,
OL,17,FAshford and its surrounding areas,
OL,18,FUlcombe, Cranbrook, Coxheath,
OL,19,FHeadcorn, Herne Bay, Charing, Challock
OL,20,Fand Molash.
OL,26,@rD@IOUrD@XO]sD@AOUtD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FMr Benton said they were delivering
OL,8,Fbottled water to vulnerable customers
OL,9,Fin areas where supplies were
OL,10,Finterrupted, or they believe there
OL,11,Fcould be problems.
OL,13,F"We have delivered 229,464 litres of
OL,14,Fwater to customers on our priority
OL,15,Fservices register, and also delivered
OL,16,Fbottled water to critical care
OL,17,Fsettings such as care homes, GP
OL,18,Fsurgeries, pharmacies and dentists,"
OL,19,Fhe said.
OL,26,@uD@AOUzD@dO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,F"Additionally, we are supporting the
OL,8,FQueen Victoria Memorial Hospital in
OL,9,FHerne Bay and urgent care unit with a
OL,10,Ftanker and supporting those with
OL,11,Flivestock.
OL,13,F"We are continuing to ask customers in
OL,14,Fsupply to use water for essential
OL,15,Fpurposes only ` for example drinking,
OL,16,Fwashing and cooking.
OL,18,F"We have bottled water collection
OL,19,Fstations already set up and are
OL,20,Freviewing these locations
OL,21,Fcontinuously."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUzD@AOU}D@NO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FWhitstable resident Julie Friel said
OL,8,Fher water supply became affected at
OL,9,Faround 6pm on Wednesday before being
OL,10,Fcompletely gone by 8pm.
OL,12,FThe 52-year-old said: "We can't wash,
OL,13,Fwe can't drink. My partner went out
OL,14,Fabout 7.30am to join the massive
OL,15,Fqueues for water.
OL,17,F"It's just wholly unacceptable on the
OL,18,Ffirst week of hot weather for this to
OL,19,Fbe happening."
OL,26,@tD@WOUyD@AOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FThe life coach, who lives with her
OL,8,Fpartner and their cat and dog, used
OL,9,Fthree two-litre bottles of water on
OL,10,FThursday morning doing washing, making
OL,11,Fbreakfast, flushing toilets and making
OL,12,Fsure the pets had drinking water.
OL,14,FShe added there is "no real
OL,15,Finformation to what's happening" and
OL,16,Fcomplained to South East Water on the
OL,17,Fphone on Wednesday evening.
OL,19,FShe said people are like "sitting
OL,20,Fducks" with water, adding it seems
OL,21,Fthere is "nothing you can do".
OL,26,@vD@TOUwD@`O]{D@ZOU|D@FO]}D@JOU}D@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,F"It's not fun having to do a real
OL,8,Fshallow kitchen sink wash when you're
OL,9,Fsweating, it is not nice," she added.
OL,11,FMark Stubbs, head chef of Wheelers
OL,12,FOyster Bar on Whitstable high street,
OL,13,Fsaid the water outage was a "bit of a
OL,14,Fshock" and the restaurant had to
OL,15,Fclose, cancel bookings and send staff
OL,16,Fhome on Thursday.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@ZO]uD@]OUvD@FO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FThe restaurant receives fresh stock on
OL,8,FThursdays but "I can't sell it", he
OL,9,Fadded, as health and safety rules
OL,10,Fmeans food outlets cannot open without
OL,11,Frunning water for hygiene reasons.
OL,13,F"Staff have had to be sent home, it's
OL,14,Fcosting a lot of money," the chef said.
OL,16,F"It's nice weather and half term when
OL,17,Fthe high street should be thriving.
OL,19,F"The hospitality industry is going to
OL,20,Fbe hit again really hard."
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@_O]uD@AOUvD@XO]xD@AOU{D@AOU|D@
OL,26,AZO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
