OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1780138973
OL,3,CThousands without water for seventh
OL,4,Cday after reservoirs 'reach critical
OL,5,Clevel'
OL,7,FThe 52-year-old said his water supply
OL,8,Fat home has also been cut off since
OL,9,FWednesday evening so he will be "going
OL,10,Fhome smelling of fish and got nowhere
OL,11,Fto wash".
OL,13,F"We haven't even had a summer, we've
OL,14,Fhad one hot hot day," he said. "So
OL,15,Fwhat is it going to be like if we have
OL,16,Fcontinual nice weather?"
OL,18,FHe said if the water outage continues
OL,19,Fit will cost the restaurant a
OL,20,F"fortune" because fresh fish is
OL,21,Fperishable so he cannot sell it.
OL,26,@qD@aOUsD@HO]uD@AOUvD@UO]vD@`OUxD@XO]|D@
OL,26,AAOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
